{"title":"How to watch Milan-San Remo 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/watch-milan-san-remo","date":1710266788000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/watch-milan-san-remo\">How to watch Milan-San Remo 2024</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-route-riders-and-all-you-need-to-know\" target=\"_blank\">Milan-San Remo</a> is the first Monument of the season and called ‘La Primavera’ (The Spring Classic) due to its early positioning in the cycling calendar. This year’s edition will be the 115th, over a distance of 288km and take place on Saturday 16th March.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 Milan-San Remo will depart from Pavia and head south towards the coast. The peloton will once again tackle the Passo del Turchino before hitting the Tre Capi (Capo Mele, Capo Cervo and Capo Berta) in the final section of the race, followed by the Cipressa and Poggio di San Remo at the business end.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year’s edition was won by Mathieu van der Poel, who won for the first time in an historic season that included wins at <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-2023-highlights\" target=\"_blank\">Paris-Roubaix</a> and the World Championships.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/from-the-archive-in-conversation-with-eddy-merckx\" target=\"_blank\">Eddy Merckx</a> is the most successful rider, winning Milan-San Remo seven times. A women’s race was <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/womens-milan-san-remo\" target=\"_blank\">previously said to be in the works</a> for 2023, but this has not come to fruition (despite no word on why not and whether it is still part of the plan, boo – at least we have <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/trofeo-alfredo-binda-preview\" target=\"_blank\">Trofeo Alfredo Binda</a>).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A stacked peloton of contenders will be taking to the start, including the defending champion Van der Poel who will be starting his season and Tadej Pogačar, who wants <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\" target=\"_blank\">Monument</a> number four.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/trofeo-alfredo-binda-preview\">Trofeo Alfredo Binda 2024: Route, TV, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-preview-favourites\">Who are the favourites for Milan-San Remo 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\">Cycling spring Classics 2024: Race dates, Monuments, cobbles and live TV guide</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-preview\">Milan-San Remo 2024: Route, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Milan-San Remo 2024 TV guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"mathieu van der poel with the milan-san remo trophy in 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-van-der-poel-milan-san-remo-2023-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Matej Mohorič is all smiles after a memorable victory in 2022</figcaption><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Milan-San Remo is being shown on Eurosport and <a href=\"https://www.discoveryplus.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> in the UK, <a href=\"https://www.max.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Max</a> and <a href=\"https://www.flobikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">FloBikes</a> in the United States, Canada can catch it on FloBike too. In Australia the races will be broadcast on <a href=\"https://www.sbs.com.au/ondemand/collection/live-and-upcoming-sport\" target=\"_blank\">SBS</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, has specific advice for watching cycling and costs £5.36 per month with three months free. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN+</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Milan-San Remo 2024 broadcast times</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times are GMT and subject to change by the broadcasters</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 08:30-17:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 09:50-17:30</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/watch-milan-san-remo\">How to watch Milan-San Remo 2024</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"jrobinson","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"1917abefcd35c689509e0c66f0cdd35128f7c9d655bde402eb91e7f8f7f31313","category":"Cycling"}